<section id="tribute-info">
<h2 id="headline">A Timeline of Toriyama's Life:</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>April 5, 1955</strong> - Akira Toriyama is born in Hepburn, Japan</li>
<li><strong>1978</strong> - Publishes first manga called Wonder Island in Weekly Shonen Jump</li>
<li><strong>1980</strong> - Publishes first succesful manga in the Weekly Shonen Jump titled Dr.Slump</li>
<li><strong>1981</strong> - Dr.Slump earns the Shogakukan Manga Award of the year</li>
<li><strong>1981</strong> - Dr.Slump gains aired anime adaptation that runs through 1981-1999</li>
<li><strong>1982</strong> - Toriyama is Married to Yoshimi Kato</li>
<li><strong>1983</strong> - A two-part manga called Dragon Boy is released</li>
<li><strong>1984</strong> - Dragon Boy becomes Dragon Ball and is released in Shonen Jump</li>
<li><strong>1984-1995</strong> - Dragon Ball Sells 159.5 million copies in Weekly Shonen Jump becoming the best-selling series of all time</li>
<li><strong>1986</strong> - Toriyama releases one-shot manga named Mr.Ho</li>
<li><strong>1988</strong> - Toriyama releases one-shot manga named Young Master Ken'nosuke</li>
<li><strong>1989</strong> - Toriyama releases one-shot manga named The Elder</li>
<li><strong>1996</strong> - Dragon Ball's 3rd animation adpation(GT) is aired</li>
<li><strong>1999-2005</strong> - Toriyama releases self-parody of Dragon Ball known as Neko Majin</li>
<li><strong>2013</strong> - Dragon Ball Z:Battle of Gods becomes Toriyama's 1st theatrical flim in 17 years</li>
<li><strong>March 1, 2024</strong> - Toriyama dies of subdural hematoma at the yound age of 68</li>
</ul>


<p id="quote">"Too much FANTASY loses REALITY, too much HOPE may seem somehow EMPTY"    
  -Akira Toriyama
</p>

<h3>If you have time and would like to learn more about Toriyama's life and works check out his <a id="tribute-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Akira_Toriyama#Early_life" target="_blank">Wikipedia Entry</a></h3>
